Exceptional software!!! Many Thanks to F.O.S.I.  I have been getting at your small assortment of files for probably 8 years now!

For F.O.S.I., EASEUS and everyone....   I just recovered all but six files on a two Terabyte disk that was only lacking about 100GB of being full! 

Buy this software!  It is the absolute best I have seen!  I picked up several new 1TB drives to recover this 2TB drive to. I struggled for days with other recovery software--I got nothing useful. 

Then I tried EASEUS and it pulled all but a few files back!  It was not fast, taking a bit over 31 hours and knowledge of what I was doing, but I have the greatest share of my data back. It was psychological research data, and to me, priceless! 

If you take your time, insure you know what you are doing first by a bit of online work to comprehend disk structure, formatting, NTSF, or Linux EXT3 formatting and all that sort of technical info, have a working disk, and you recover to a different partition than the scrambled data was on, you will probably get your data back using EASEUS.  

Oh yes, a good old trick I should pass along.  

If the disk quits, makes noise, such as loud clicking, and won't read. You think it is shot and it contains important data that may cost a bag of gold to professionally recover, here is a real trick.    

Place the HDD in the freezer for three hours, then pull it, immediately hook it up and go to work with recovery. 

You are likely to be successful until the disk begins to heat up. When it does, back in the freezer for an hour (maybe two) and then back in the machine for more recovery. 

Repeat as necessary.

I once recovered the majority of an unreadable 800GB disk using this method!  Took a bit of time, but certainly made me happy.
